b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe46024.htm)  [Next](sbe46026.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n[Buy this Book at\nAmazon.com](http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/0543983846/internetsacredte)\n\n* * *\n\n[![](../../img/tn_hin.jpg)](index.htm)  \n_Vedic Hymns, Part II (SBE46)_ , by Hermann Oldenberg [1897], at sacred-\ntexts.com\n\n* * *\n\np. 95\n\n### MA _N_ _D_ ALA I, HYMN 75.\n\n#### ASH _T_ AKA I, ADHY\xc3\x82YA 5, VARGA .3.\n\n1\\. Accept gladly our most widely-sounding [1](sbe46025.htm#an_1:75:1:1)\nspeech, the most agreeable to the gods, thou who, in thy mouth, offerest the\nsacrificial food (to the gods).\n\n2\\. And may we then pronounce to thee, O highest A\xe1\xb9\x85giras, Agni, best\nworshipper, a prayer agreeable to thee and successful.\n\n3\\. Who is thy kinsman among men, O Agni? Who performs worship to thee\n[1](sbe46025.htm#an_1:75:3:1)? Who art thou, and where dost thou rest?\n\n4\\. Thou, O Agni, art the kinsman, the dear friend ('Mitra') of men, a friend\nwho is to be magnified by his friends.\n\n5\\. Sacrifice for us to Mitra and Varu _n_ a. Sacrifice to the gods, (a\nsacrifice conforming to) the great _Ri_ ta [1](sbe46025.htm#an_1:75:5:1).\nSacrifice, O Agni, to thy own house.\n\n#### NOTES.\n\nThe same _Ri_ shi and metre.--Verse 1 = TB. III, 6, 7, 1; MS. III, 10, 1 (IV,\n13, 5). Verses 3-5 = SV. II, 885-887\\. Verse 5. = VS. XXXIII, 3; TB. II, 7,\n12, 1.\n\n##### Verse 1.\n\nNote 1. Comp. VI, 68, 9. manma \xe2\x80\xa6 sapratha _h_.\n\n##### Verse 3.\n\nNote 1. May we not take da _s_ u-adhvara as a compound with governed final\nmember, like vidadvasu, sadadyoni &c.?\n\n##### Verse 5.\n\nNote 1. Comp. Gaedicke, Der Accusativ im Veda, 159.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: I, 76](sbe46026.htm)\n\n"